    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.2.60-66"/>
                <note type="curatorial">60</note>
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                
                <note type="authorial">Just read a letter from Kreider. Says he loves me "better than Jesus"!!</note>
                
                <fw type="authorial">
                    The Florence
                    JM HITCHINGS 
                    PROPRIETOR
                    Missoula, Montana.
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    
                    <dateline>
                        Dec 5 21 
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Ones:-</salute>
                    
                </opener>
                
                <p>I recieved all your letters a moment ago, I can tell <unclear/></p>
                <p>(Tuesday) Can stay a day or so with Grace, I'm happy to say.</p>
                <p>I <unclear/> Kearney, Ashburg for an engagement for Dec 9th. You see, since <unclear/> failed to get
                Kearney &amp;</p> 
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.2.60-66"/>
                <note type="curatorial">61</note>
                <note type="authorial">-2-</note>
                
                <fw type="authorial">
                    The Florence
                    JM HITCHINGS 
                    PROPRIETOR
                    Missoula, Montana.
                </fw>
                
                <p>Lincoln, I'm hit hard. I'm going to refuse to pay full commission to Feobius. He has done nothing
                for me. I'll get home with just about 18,200 in spite of the loss of Kearney &amp; Lincoln (How Feobius
                failed I can't guess). But out of the 200 comes Feobius' commission. You'll see from this that I
                really haven't spend excessively. I spent only $1.40 on Sterling in a week.</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.2.60-66"/>
                <note type="curatorial">62</note>
                <note type="authorial">-3-</note>
                
                <fw type="authorial">
                    The Florence
                    JM HITCHINGS 
                    PROPRIETOR
                    Missoula, Montana.
                </fw>
               
               <p>I wouldn't care, except that I waited to have enough for the payment, But we'll get through. After
               all, I shall have been making, all together, over $40 per week while absent.</p>
               <p>I'm to dine with the head of the English department &amp; Maurice Brown of the Fittle Theater, Chicago,
               this evening. Damn dining!</p>
               <p>Kisses for all my precious Wubs. It was so very good</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.2.60-66"/>
                <note type="curatorial">63</note>
                <note type="authorial">-4-</note>
                
                <fw type="authorial">
                    The Florence
                    JM HITCHINGS 
                    PROPRIETOR
                    Missoula, Montana.
                </fw>
                
                <p>of my beautiful good big girl ro send me persimmions. It was like eating a piece of home! And I'm so
                glad Sig is being a fine little man, as a I knew he would. I jave seen the country through which Sig
                and I will make a pack-horse trip in four years or five from now. It will be over
                the Nez Perce trail through the wild wild Bitter Root mountains. It will take two weeks to</p> 
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.2.60-66"/>
                <note type="curatorial">64</note>
                <note type="authorial">-5-</note>
                
                <fw type="authorial">
                    The Florence
                    JM HITCHINGS 
                    PROPRIETOR
                    Missoula, Montana.
                </fw>
                
                <p>break through the wilderness into <unclear/>, There'll be deer &amp; bears to shoot. Blessed <unclear/>!
                What a dear letter she wrote me! Daddy knew just what it said!</p>
                <p>Mama, I've written a number of letters to you alone. It's hard to do correspondence properly on such
                a trip. I think a great deal of you, never doubt. Don't worry about money. We'll be all right, &amp; we
                must</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.2.60-66"/>
                <note type="curatorial">65</note>
                <note type="authorial">-6-</note>
                
                <fw type="authorial">
                    The Florence
                    JM HITCHINGS 
                    PROPRIETOR
                    Missoula, Montana.
                </fw>
                
                <p>be good Socialists. I'm more Socialist than ever. The world at present is a fool. Mona girl, your
                flaws sound perfectly bully! That sleeping porch idea is a corker, surely. It's just the thing for
                that country. I doubt if you people realize how "classy" the Ozarks are as to scenery. Really,
                Branson is a beaty spot, even</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.2.60-66"/>
                <note type="curatorial">66</note>
                <note type="authorial">-7-</note>
                
                <fw type="authorial">
                    The Florence
                    JM HITCHINGS 
                    PROPRIETOR
                    Missoula, Montana.
                </fw>
                
                <p>when compared with famous Western places. It's a bully place to live!</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>So much love to all.</salute>
                    <signed>Jno</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
